<headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 31 at 2:56PM MDT  by NWS Saltlake</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of southwestern Beaver
and northwestern Iron Counties through 400 PM MDT...
At 255 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 8
miles east of Ursine, moving northeast at 10 mph.
HAZARD...Nickel size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.
Locations impacted include...
Hamlin Valley.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.88 IN
MAX WIND GUST...&lt;40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.
Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
